                                                   Arjuna view

           
	Colombo: Sri Lanka Cricket (SLC) chief and World Cup-winning captain Arjuna Ranatunga called for a revamp of the umpiring system in international matches on Sunday. 
    
	My personal view is that two local umpires must officiate with the ICC panel umpire sitting in the box with the Match Referee, Ranatunga said. (AFP) 
                                                   
